social_posts.post_text: It’s an incredibly painful process of centering myself - to put myself first, to expand my light, to not be small to accommodate other people’s feelings because I have to face the fear of abandonment. I’m conditioned to believe that I’ll say or do the wrong things and others will dislike me. And everything was a reward system to me - I have to do ten things for this one person in order to be rewarded with affection. But the discomfort of not knowing who I am is increasing to the point of feeling so sick of everything. Just heard this from @wenzes_ and it’s so helpful, “I like people if they like me for who I am. People have to like me for me liking myself. I am the center of my universe.”

I’ve been testing/playing with #AI generated images using a phone app called Dream by Wombo and been posting them here. It’s been a week now, I think, and finally trying a different generator. This one is from #lexica. I’m still in the learning phase, but this one seems to prefer very vibrant colors. I used words like “soft color tone” or “monochrome” or “pastel aesthetic”… Nothing changed. I had to process the images to tone down the vibrancy a bit. I do like that, comparing Midjourney, the site is nice and “quiet” meaning I don’t see other users’ creations except my own. Overall, the quality is great and worth giving a try. // For full size images, check out my stories.

Gave #midjourney another try today. It’s definitely more powerful because of the larger amount of users using it, which means a lot more data collected. I was able to get the results that I like from one try - lighting, atmosphere, color tone are on point. If you don’t mind the chaotic interface, this is a great one to try. #AI

More from #lexica - I quite like the clothing pieces it created from the prompt I gave. The images came out pretty stabilized. My only complain, which I mentioned before, is the colors. It’s too vibrant for me. It doesn’t have enough users to collect the data. The prompt “in the style of Wes Anderson movies” would result in different color tones between Lexica and Midjourney. Midjourney would know to use pastel candy like colors, but not Lexica. #AI // Extra images and in full length are on my stories.

Part 3 of this series of a seaside community that I visited through my imagination. Part of being a photographer is often times I need to come up with a shoot idea. Using #AI generated images, I came up with a storyboard of a community of retirees living by the ocean. Everyday is an occasion for them. And they’re busy tending to their gardens, visiting each other for tea or lunch, having bingo nights, dancing, talking, reminiscing… I’m still new at this, so I wasn’t successful at having pets by their side or in their arms (the animals looked deformed), but let’s imagine most of them have pets that they love. Sometimes there are dramas, but things always work out in the end. Imagine this limited series being shown on BBC and PBS. It needs a name. What should it be?

Watched The Banshees of Inisherin last weekend and I’m still thinking about it. To be brutally honest, “I don’t want to be friends with you anymore.” Or to be nice, make compromise and maybe keep a distance. The thing is… when someone no longer brings you joy or shares same ideas/values, then seeing each other just becomes a chore of small talk. We don’t know if there’s a tomorrow, so if we use up today to make sure another person is happy or comfortable, then is it a disservice to our lives? But then the conversation always ends up with we should be nice to others. We should make time for another human being, love others like you love yourself. Regardless, it’s hurtful to say and hear, “I don’t want to be friends with you anymore.” // #AI

Created an art installation to bring awareness that nature will still thrive This was 2 months ago, when I just started playing with #AI generated images. I made so many Audrey Hepburn inspired dolls and came up with wardrobes that I’d want to have for myself. 

I was one of those who were against using AI, but thought - “let me try it before judging it.” Didn’t know it would open a portal to a place where I feel… belong. Having grew up with a narcissistic parent, I learned to dissociate from reality and lived in my imagination to cope. Also having grew up in a Chinese family, the male child of the family is more favorable, so I didn’t have dolls to play with; it was mostly car toys. And I wasn’t allowed to pursuit fashion design because I wouldn’t be able to make a living. They didn’t think I was smart enough to be a doctor or lawyer, but didn’t give me guidance either, so I just floated through life with no life goal. 

But what is meant for you will always find its way to you. All the twist and turn, I became a photographer and get to live that artist life I felt strongly for. With the things I lacked in early life + the things I gained later, and now with this new tool I can release what’s kept inside of me secretly for so long.

So here it is: a doll, fashion design and imagination.

Fight or Flight *** You always thought something is wrong with you. Can’t keep a relationship. You want to be loved, but have commitment issue. You want to be touched, but runaway from closenesses. You are always in fight or flight mode. “It’s better to be alone,” you thought. 

One day, you heard a little voice. “Hey, wake up.” 

You investigated, dug deep into the past, into your most inner self. Old memories came back. Childhood wasn’t as cheerful as you saw from the old picture albums. The fear, worries, shame, loneliness that your little self is carrying throughout your life is becoming clearer and clearer.

Mystery is solved. You are not a bad person. Turns out you were just a protector to your little self, not wanting her to get hurt again.
———————————————
I have been working on myself for about ten years, but only recently things have became more clear. I love metaphor, so using #AI to help create scenes that depict what it’s like to live with childhood trauma.

Sharing my creative process with using #Midjourney #AI as more people are DM-ing me about it. If you’re interested in it, highly recommend searching the internet and YouTube where you’ll find plenty of resources to get you started.

I first started with an app, Dream by Wombo, about 2 months ago. Once I “mastered” the app, I moved onto Midjourney about a month ago. That was a big learning curve. I’m still watching YouTube tutorials every morning.

From this set of slides, I started with an idea: a mushroom type creature with an umbrella. If I like what I’m seeing I might change what I don’t like, usually is the color accent or background. Sometimes I might not like how the color tone comes out, so I’d change to cooler or warmer tone by using different lighting. When I really love something I’d change color tones to get different looks/feel. Check out my previous last 3 posts. They all came from the same prompt, but different color accents. Once I collected enough good images I might change the prompt a bit by deleting/replacing few words or change the season or change the day of time. For ex: same prompt, but add “summer morning” or “nightlife.” Today I got bored and changed a human girl to a cat.

This process took about a day and generated about 3-4 different stories for me.

Hope this helps. Have fun!

Grew up in Hong Kong back in 70s-80s, my parents would put on these Chinese folklore type of tv shows on. Some were fascinating (deep sea creatures of warriors and princesses) and some were scary (ghosts and unkind creatures). Til this day I cannot sleep without covering my feet because one of the shows had a ghost killed a man from poking holes under his feet! Sahara Desert, lands of the Kioo Cha Bluu. 
[prompt word suggested by @bonnietsang — crystals]

3 March 2051, 9.27 pm.

Since the exodus of T'cha back when the war began 20 years ago, the African tribes that travelled throughout the Sahara Desert following their new Messiah disappeared.

This event has gone lost in the history because right after the exodus started, the Third World War fell down on mankind.

But where did they all go?

From glimpse of understanding, we now know that all of them were being called in a particular place on earth, in the core of the Sahara Desert, where something precise was calling them, attracting them.

A something that T'cha was dependent of, a blue crystal emanating radiations all around it. An otherworldly material of which origins are lost in time and universe. Presumably, part of an old asteroid or, more than that, part of what made the universe come to life when existence began.

It's supposed to be the element that stimulated the infamous Big Bang where all things started.

This blue crystal had morphed, carved and possessed all those who gathered from all part of Africa, called by the Manifesto that T'cha gave to his Nations.

Humans and crystals are now a oneness. Their skin is blue, their body transformed into hybrids between flesh and crystal, and they communicate using gravity as their language. They can send waves into the gravity asset, signalling pathways and convey messages throughout kilometres, and maybe lightyears too.

They own time, space, and are a bridge between humanity and gods. Or so it's thought to be.

They are the population of Kioo Cha Bluu, that literally could be translated in old Swahili as the Population of the Blue Crystal.

Night and day, they wander and live beneath the underground and the desert, creating mines and caves in which they plant pieces of crystals directly from their body into the dirt or sand.

They help the Crystal to spread.

Testing #midjourneyv5 on various settings - outdoor, indoor, portrait, light sources, close-up, and wide angle. Here’s an imaginary 1960s cafe inside a cathedral.

Compare to V4, image quality from V5 is much better. Face doesn’t get distorted in wide angle. Body movement looks less robotic. However, and this is going to be strange negative comment, the end result is too pretty. I know, that’s what most users want - ultra realistic photos. The problem for me is if I want to make strange looking things, it’s not doing it for me. I even like the extra fingers and legs! 😆 So I’ll be switching between V4 and V5 a lot. Regardless, awesome job that #Midjourney did.

I’ve been channeling and today a father came through for a daughter. His message brought hope and peace.

SPIRIT MESSAGE: RISE UP // You’ve covered yourself up for so long that perhaps you’ve  forgotten how amazing you are. 

Maybe growing up an adult said, “Don’t do that, you’re not going to make any money.” Or a classmate said, “You like that? That’s weird.” Years and years of shrinking and disguising turned you into someone else. 

The Universe is saying, “ENOUGH! It’s time to rise up and show your truth self.”

It’s scary to uncover yourself and stand up tall. Quite a few people will not like your change. And quite a few people will disappoint you. But when you let your light shine, the right people will find you. You won’t need to chase, you’ll just attract.

You are loved. Your spirit guide is there to support you.
